718517f-a.title: Manhattan: Central Park West - 96th Street
718517f-a.text:
Scotch Presbyterian Church, Central Park West at S.W. corner of 96th Street. This structure was demolished in the fall of 1928
to make way for an apartment house.
July 10, 1928.
P. L. Sperr.

714883f-a.title: Manhattan: 96th Street - Central Park West
714883f-a.text:
96th Street, south side, west from Central Park West.
May 23, 1929.
P. L. Sperr.

718518f-a.title: Manhattan: Central Park West - 96th Street
718518f-a.text:
First Church of Christ Scientist, Central Park West at N.W. corner of 96th Street, seen across the ruin of the Scotch
Presbyterian Church.
October, 1928.
P. L. Sperr.
(2)
The same, from Central Park.
February 2, 1929.
P. L. Sperr.
